Related to issue [Fixes #6858] Changes to MvcOption's settings (SuppressInputFormatterBuffering & AllowBindingUndefinedValueToEnumType) are not taking affect

@dougbu @pranavkm I missed the xml formatters in my earlier PR and this fixes that.

I found this bug today while working on a different issue. The following piece of code doesn't cause the affect that you would expect them to:

```c#
services.AddMvc(o =>
{
    o.AllowBindingUndefinedValueToEnumType = true; // was added post 2.0 release
    o.SuppressInputFormatterBuffering = true; // is part of 2.0 release
});
```

This is because the following pieces of code get executed even before the above option manipulation occurs causing the affects not to be seen:

https://github.com/aspnet/Mvc/blob/dev/src/Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Core/Internal/MvcCoreMvcOptionsSetup.cs#L49
https://github.com/aspnet/Mvc/blob/dev/src/Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Formatters.Json/Internal/MvcJsonMvcOptionsSetup.cs#L80


**Workaround:**
Sequence the `Configure<MvcOptions>` method before the `AddMvc` method

```c#
services.Configure<MvcOptions>(o =>
{
    o.AllowBindingUndefinedValueToEnumType = true;
    o.SuppressInputFormatterBuffering = true;
});

services.AddMvc();
```

**Fix**: 
Pass around MvcOptions instance rather than the actual value. Any mutation to MvcOptions can be observed by individual components

